headline: Foreign language learning holds strong against the AI wave
description: Artificial intelligence now translates both spoken and written language with ease and at lightning speed. Yet, it still lacks 'culture' and the human touch needed to free employees from mastering English – or any other foreign language – in the workplace.

headline: Six Nations: France faces Irish challenge in tournament opener
description: After struggling in recent months, the French men's rugby team opens its defense of the Six Nations Championship on Thursday against Ireland. The match offers a major test for Fabien Galthié to fine-tune his squad ahead of the 2027 Rugby World Cup.

headline: Lore Baudrit, captain of France's Olympic women's hockey team: 'We train like pros, but don't get paid'
description: The forward, who has played 250 times for the national team, was set to take part in the first Olympic tournament of her career starting Thursday. Like most of her teammates, she has to juggle life as a top-level athlete with a day job.

headline: Gabriella Papadakis, ice dancer: 'My mother turned me into a little soldier who let herself be guided by the decisions of others'
description: 'I wouldn't be where I am today if...' In this series, Le Monde interviews a personality about a decisive moment in their life. The figure skater and former Olympic champion looks back on a childhood filled with constraints in order to succeed in a demanding and conservative environment.

headline: Jeffrey Epstein's business ties with banker Ariane de Rothschild revealed
description: The latest release of the Epstein files by the US Department of Justice has confirmed the extremely close relationship between the French-German head of the Edmond de Rothschild group and the convicted sex offender. From 2013 until his death in 2019, he acted as an unofficial adviser to the Switzerland-based bank.
